Date: 1999-08-09

Title: Vortex solution in 2+1 dimensional Yang-Mills theory at high

temperaturesAuthors: Dmitri Diakonov (NORDITA and St.Petersburg NPI)

Comments: 8 p., three .eps figures included

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A14 (1999) 1909-1916

At high temperatures the A_0 component of the Yang--Mills field plays therole of the Higgs field, and the 1-loop potential V(A_0) plays the role of theHiggs potential. We find a new stable vortex solution of theAbrikosov-Nielsen-Olesen type, and discuss its properties and possibleimplications.